  "body": "I currently have a setup where I need to run tests sometimes in Truffle, sometimes in Buidler. Therefore I have this kind of code in my tests\r\n\r\n```\r\nbefore(async () => {\r\n    const myLib = await MyLib.new();\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n      await MyContract1.link(MyLib);\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      // running in buidler, use instance\r\n      await MyContract1.link(myLib);\r\n    }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be great to have the same syntax for both.",
